text: Johnson County is a county in the U.S. state of Illinois. According to the 2020 census, it has a population of 13,308. The county seat is Vienna. Johnson County was founded in 1812 and named for Richard M. Johnson, who was then a U.S. Congressman from Kentucky. == References == Category:1810s establishments in Illinois Territory Category:1812 establishments in the United States Category:Illinois counties
title: Johnson County, Illinois
